'''May 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840|1=tomobiki}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Reiki (era)|en|Reiki (era)|qid=Q1373115|lt=Reiki|1=Reiki (era)}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|716|en|716|qid=Q23531|lt=716|1=716}} {{ill|June 10|en|June 10|qid=Q2615|lt=June 10|1=June 10}}) – The Eastern court relocated 1,799 people of Goguryeo origin to Musashi and established the {{ill|Kōrai-gun|ja|高麗郡|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōrai-gun|1=Koma district|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11673318}}.
* {{ill|Genki (era)|en|Genki (era)|qid=Q1145064|lt=Genki|1=Genki (era)}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1571|en|1571|qid=Q6666|lt=1571|1=1571}} {{ill|June 8|en|June 8|qid=Q2621|lt=June 8|1=June 8}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|en|Oda Nobunaga|qid=Q171411|lt=Oda Nobunaga|1=Oda Nobunaga}} attacked the stronghold of the Ise-based {{ill|Sieges of Nagashima|en|Sieges of Nagashima|qid=Q1073030|lt=Chōshū Ikki|1=Sieges of Nagashima}} at {{ill|Ganshōji|ja|願証寺|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ganshōji|1=Q11665171|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11665171}}, suffering heavy losses led by {{ill|Ujiie Naomoto|en|Ujiie Naomoto|qid=Q7878198|lt=Ujige Naomoto|1=Ujiie Naomoto}}.
* {{ill|Kansei|en|Kansei|qid=Q1195131|lt=Kansei|1=Kansei}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1792|en|1792|qid=Q7805|lt=1792|1=1792}} {{ill|July 4|en|July 4|qid=Q2698|lt=July 4|1=July 4}}) – The publication of Hayashikodaira's work, 【Kaikoku Heidan】, was banned; its author, Hayashikodaira, was subsequently imprisoned.
* {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|qid=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|March 26|en|March 26|qid=Q2456|lt=March 26|1=March 26}}) – The British Minister of Foreign Affairs, reported as part of the 【Chūgoku Shinbun】 (later published as a special extra) covering the events of the restoration.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kanbun (era)|en|Kanbun (era)|qid=Q1146228|lt=Kanbun|1=Kanbun (era)}} 6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1666|en|1666|qid=Q7585|lt=1666|1=1666}} {{ill|June 18|en|June 18|qid=Q2670|lt=June 18|1=June 18}}) – {{ill|Manabe Akifusa|en|Manabe Akifusa|qid=Q6746560|lt=Mamabe Senbō|1=Manabe Akifusa}}, the first lord of the Murakami Domain in Echigo (died {{ill|1720|en|1720|qid=Q6908|lt=1720|1=1720}}).
* {{ill|Enkyō (Edo period)|en|Enkyō (Edo period)|qid=Q1183728|lt=Enkyō|1=Enkyō (Edo period)}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1744|en|1744|qid=Q7583|lt=1744|1=1744}} {{ill|June 26|en|June 26|qid=Q2661|lt=June 26|1=June 26}}) – {{ill|Mizuno Tadayoshi|ja|水野忠鼎|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizuno Tadayoshi|1=Mizuno Tadakane|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q10565568}}, the second lord of the Karatsu Domain (died {{ill|1818|en|1818|qid=Q6964|lt=1818|1=1818}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1575|en|1575|qid=Q6688|lt=1575|1=1575}} {{ill|June 24|en|June 24|qid=Q2665|lt=June 24|1=June 24}}) – {{ill|Torii Suneemon|en|Torii Suneemon|qid=Q2337176|lt=Torii Qiyūemon|1=Torii Suneemon}}, a samurai (born {{ill|1540|en|1540|qid=Q6482|lt=1540|1=1540}}).
* {{ill|Genna|en|Genna|qid=Q635245|lt=Genna|1=Genna}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1623|en|1623|qid=Q6818|lt=1623|1=1623}} {{ill|June 13|en|June 13|qid=Q2614|lt=June 13|1=June 13}}) – {{ill|Hon'inbō Sansa|en|Hon'inbō Sansa|qid=Q2656780|lt=Hon'inbō Sansa|1=Hon'inbō Sansa}}, an accomplished go player and the first head of the Hon'inbō house (born {{ill|1559|en|1559|qid=Q6609|lt=1559|1=1559}}).
* {{ill|Bunka|en|Bunka|qid=Q1373146|lt=Bunka|1=Bunka}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1807|en|1807|qid=Q6909|lt=1807|1=1807}} {{ill|June 21|en|June 21|qid=Q2671|lt=June 21|1=June 21}}) – {{ill|Minagawa Kien|ja|皆川淇園|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minagawa Kien|1=Ki-en|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q3196280}}, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q125199930}}) (born {{ill|1734|en|1734|qid=Q6977|lt=1734|1=1734}}).

